verbs.description: By MARC A. THIESSEN WASHINGTON -- [ARG2: How evil] [V: is] [ARG1: MS-13] ? Last year , two gang members in Texas reportedly murdered a teenage girl as an offering to Satan . According to prosecutors , the gang leader ( known as " Diabolico " ) told the young girl that " the Beast " wanted " a soul " before having his partner shoot her in the head and dump her body on a street corner . As charges were read against the two , the Houston Chronicle reported , they " laughed , smiled and waved for the media cameras . " MS-13 gang members , police have said , also stabbed a Maryland man more than 100 times before decapitating him and cutting out his heart ... lured a 34-year - old man to his already dug grave ... and stoned an 18-year - old boy to death and dumped his body under a bridge . MS-13 is a demonic death cult . And President Trump has Nancy Pelosi defending its members ' humanity . When Trump declared at a White House roundtable " You would n't believe how bad these people are . These are n't people . These are animals , " he was clearly referring to MS-13 . But the media and Democrats took the president 's quote out of context and declared that he had referred to all illegal immigrants as animals ....
